<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="4"><o:p>
&nbsp;</o:p>
</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="4">5. Once the user
begins chatting, possibly outlining the topics they wish to discuss, the user
can Push web content to the other users. <o:p>
</o:p>
</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="4">This user would
like to look into Pitt's Computer Science department.<o:p>
</o:p>
</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="4">Therefore, the
user has typed the web address of the department into the Publish Tab’s Main
Page text field in order to Push the web page to the students.<o:p>
</o:p>
</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="4"><o:p>
&nbsp;</font><font size="4">Notice the other text fields present. The Publish
panel is capable of pushing three different types of content (<st1:place>
Main</st1:place>
, Audio, and Video).<o:p>
</o:p>
</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="4"><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape
 id="_x0000_i1026" type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:414.75pt;height:381pt'>
 <v:imagedata src="file:///C:/DOCUME~1/nys/LOCALS~1/Temp/msohtml1/01/clip_image003.png"
  o:title=""/>
</v:shape><![endif]-->
<img src="images/5.htm10.jpg" v:shapes="_x0000_i1026" width="553" height="508"><o:p>
</o:p>
</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="4"><o:p>
&nbsp;</o:p>
</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="4"><o:p>
&nbsp;</o:p>
</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="4">6. But first the
user would like to preview the page and make sure it is appropriate to be Pushed
to the classroom.<o:p>
</o:p>
</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="4"><o:p>
&nbsp;</o:p>
</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="4"><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape
 id="_x0000_i1027" type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:414.75pt;height:381pt'>
 <v:imagedata src="file:///C:/DOCUME~1/nys/LOCALS~1/Temp/msohtml1/01/clip_image005.png"
  o:title=""/>
</v:shape><![endif]-->
<img src="images/5.htm11.jpg" v:shapes="_x0000_i1027" width="553" height="508"><o:p>
</o:p>
</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="4"><o:p>
&nbsp;</o:p>
</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="4">7. The user can
pose questions to the class and respond via the provided emoticon icons of the
classroom. These icons express feelings and emotions. In this instance the user
is agreeing that they should have a discussion.<o:p>
</o:p>
</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="4"><o:p>
&nbsp;</o:p>
</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="4">* Not shown is the
private chat capability of the Teacher Tool. It is similar to the general chat
capability of the Tool except that no one can see the message except for the
intended recipient.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp; </span>This feature is
accessed via the To: drop down menu*<o:p>
</o:p>
</font></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="4"><o:p>
&nbsp;</o:p>
</font></p>
<p style="line-height: 150%"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; mso-fareast-font-family: PMingLiU; mso-font-kerning: 1.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ZH-TW; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><font size="4">**
The user is also capable of delivering their messages in audio via the
integrated text to speech agent of the Student Tool. All one must do is check
the audio checkbox.**</font></span>
